{"abstract":[{"text":"Performs a logical AND operation on two Boolean values.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"&&"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"lhs"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"rhs"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"attribute","text":"@autoclosure"},{"kind":"text","text":" () "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"rethrows"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","identifier":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The left-hand side of the operation."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"lhs"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The right-hand side of the operation."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"rhs"}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The logical AND operator ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"&&"},{"type":"text","text":") combines two Boolean values and returns"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if both of the values are "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":". If either of the values is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", the operator returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This operator uses short-circuit evaluation: The left-hand side ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lhs"},{"type":"text","text":") is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"evaluated first, and the right-hand side ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rhs"},{"type":"text","text":") is evaluated only if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lhs"},{"type":"text","text":" evaluates to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":". For example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let measurements = [7.44, 6.51, 4.74, 5.88, 6.27, 6.12, 7.76]","let sum = measurements.reduce(0, +)","","if measurements.count > 0 && sum / Double(measurements.count) < 6.5 {","    print(\"Average measurement is less than 6.5\")","}","// Prints \"Average measurement is less than 6.5\""]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In this example, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lhs"},{"type":"text","text":" tests whether "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"measurements.count"},{"type":"text","text":" is greater than"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"zero. Evaluation of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"&&"},{"type":"text","text":" operator is one of the following:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"measurements.count"},{"type":"text","text":" is equal to zero, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lhs"},{"type":"text","text":" evaluates to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rhs"},{"type":"text","text":" is not evaluated, preventing a divide-by-zero error in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"expression "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sum / Double(measurements.count)"},{"type":"text","text":". The result of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operation is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"measurements.count"},{"type":"text","text":" is greater than zero, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lhs"},{"type":"text","text":" evaluates to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rhs"},{"type":"text","text":" is evaluated. The result of evaluating "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rhs"},{"type":"text","text":" is the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"result of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"&&"},{"type":"text","text":" operation."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"kind":"content"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Transforming-a-Boolean","identifiers":["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool/toggle()","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool/!(_:)","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool/__(_:_:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Transforming a Boolean"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool/&&(_:_:)"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift","doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Bool"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["/documentation/swift/bool/&&(_:_:)"]}],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:Sb2aaoiyS2b_SbyKXKtKFZ","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"&&"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"attribute","text":"@autoclosure"},{"kind":"text","text":" () "},{"kind":"keyw